20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2201dd88ca-3d51-42f6-98f0-9fb38a8a4234%5C%22%3EI%20made%20millions%20doing%20debt%20settlement%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20court%2C%20the%20bankruptcy%20lawyer%20said%20something%20to%20me%20that%20I%20still%20can't%20believe%3A%20%26quot%3BI'll%20see%20you%20again.%26quot%3B%20I%20walked%20to%20my%20car%2C%20crying%20angry%20tears%20and%20vowing%20to%20prove%20him%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERyan%20and%20I%20moved%20into%20a%20rental%20and%20tried%20to%20regroup.%20We%20started%20a%20new%20company%20with%20our%20boss%2C%20helping%20other%20people%20settle%20their%20debts.%20I%20wanted%20to%20turn%20our%20hardship%20into%20an%20opportunity%20and%20help%20others.%20Our%20company%20settled%20debt%20for%2042%25%20of%20what%20was%20owed.%20The%20consumers%20paid%20us%20a%2025%25%20fee%20to%20do%20so.%20They%20ended%20up%20paying%20about%2067%25%20of%20what%20they%20owed%2C%20plus%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-cards%2Fhow-to-get-a-lower-interest-rate-on-credit-cards%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eavoiding%20a%20lot%20of%20interest%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20business%20was%20immediately%20successful.%20When%20our%20landlord%20told%20us%20he%20would%20sell%20our%20house%2C%20Ryan%20and%20I%20could%20pay%20cash%20for%20it%20within%20a%20year.%20After%20two%20years%2C%20we%20were%20millionaires%2C%20and%20today%20our%20net%20worth%20is%20about%20%2450%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22366ae4be-17e0-423a-9e50-0fb73271e6e1%5C%22%3EI've%20rethought%20financial%20security%20and%20borrowing%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20of%20my%20experience%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-does-gen-z-want-workplace-financial-stability-paid-leave-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EI%20think%20about%20financial%20security%3C%2Fa%3E%20very%20differently%20than%20I%20used%20to.%20I%20start%20every%20day%20as%20if%20I'm%20at%20zero.%20I%20try%20to%20live%20below%20my%20means%20even%20now.%20We%20could%20have%20planes%20or%20multiple%20homes%2C%20but%20I%20never%20want%20my%20income%20today%20to%20impact%20my%20lifestyle%20going%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20met%20Ryan%2C%20he%20was%20a%20saver%2C%20and%20he%20taught%20me%20how%20to%20make%20saving%20fun.%20I%20try%20to%20pass%20this%20on%20to%20others.%20One%20way%20is%20to%20track%20your%20daily%20spending%20and%20income%20and%20make%20it%20into%20a%20game.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20determine%20whether%20you're%20in%20the%20red%20or%20the%20green.%20Doing%20that%20for%2030%20days%20can%20really%20give%20you%20insight%20into%20your%20finances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20now%20pay%20cash%20for%20almost%20everything.%20Following%20the%20bankruptcy%2C%20we%20had%20to%20do%20that%20since%20our%20credit%20was%20impacted%20for%20seven%20years.%20During%20that%20time%2C%20it%20became%20a%20habit.%20We%20no%20longer%20leverage%20the%20bank's%20money.%20We%20recently%20took%20out%20a%20mortgage%20for%20a%20second%20home%2C%20but%20we%20put%2050%25%20down.%20Owning%20at%20least%2050%25%20of%20your%20properties%20is%20a%20smarter%20way%20to%20invest%20in%20real%20estate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2249bf9cc7-30aa-457e-8629-a77ba433fcb9%5C%22%3EAs%20a%20multimillionaire%2C%20I%20returned%20to%20college%20to%20finish%20my%20degree%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20my%20kids%20are%2016%2C%2017%2C%2019%2C%2020%2C%20and%2028.%20They're%20all%20so%20different.%20My%20oldest%20daughter%20saw%20us%20go%20from%20famine%20to%20feast%20practically%20overnight.%20She%20thought%20it%20was%20easy%20and%20that%20everyone%20could%20do%20it.%20When%20she%20married%20a%20pastor%2C%20she%20was%20surprised%20to%20learn%20that%20most%20people%20weren't%20making%20six%20figures%20every%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20dropped%20out%20of%20college%20way%20back%20in%20the%20'90s.%20When%20my%20kids%20started%20considering%20college%2C%20they'd%20look%20at%20me%20and%20ask%2C%20%26quot%3BWhy%20do%20we%20need%20to%20go%3F%26quot%3B%20They%20could%20see%20that%20financial%20success%20could%20happen%20without%20a%20degree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20turn%20the%20question%20back%20on%20them%3A%20With%20parents%20willing%20to%20pay%20for%20college%2C%20why%20wouldn't%20you%20go%3F%20You%20can%20succeed%20without%20a%20degree%2C%20but%20college%20can%20also%20be%20a%20gateway%20to%20great%20relationships%20and%20learning%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20I%20went%20back%20to%20college%20and%20graduated%20in%202022.%20It%20was%20less%20about%20the%20degree%20and%20more%20about%20achieving%20my%20goal.%20I've%20shown%20that%20you%20can%20overcome%20financial%20hurdles%20without%20guilt%20or%20shame%2C%20then%20accomplish%20your%20dreams.%20It's%20never%20too%20late%20to%20finish%20what%20you%20started.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwo-years-after-declaring-bankruptcy-i-was-a-millionaire-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1748870941000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68062f40c6ad288d147ea9f0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwo-years-after-declaring-bankruptcy-i-was-a-millionaire-2025-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Amber%20Duncan%20had%20to%20declare%20bankruptcy%20in%202008%20after%20the%20financial%20crisis.%20She%20founded%20a%20debt%20settlement%20company%20with%20her%20husband.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Kelly%20Burch)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A68%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwo-years-after-declaring-bankruptcy-i-was-a-millionaire-2025-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22RGV%3A%20Vidhu%20Vinod%20Chopra%20%E2%80%98believes%20he%E2%80%99s%20the%20best%20filmmaker%E2%80%99%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1748870901000%2C%22visual%22%3