0uncertainty%20is%20forcing%20firms%20to%20stockpile%20and%20freeze%20prices.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EInflation%20cooled%20as%20businesses%20are%20delaying%20price%20hikes%20amid%20trade%20policy%20confusion.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETreasury%20Sec.%20Scott%20Bessent%20said%20there's%20no%20price%20hikes%20yet%2C%20but%20firms%20are%20adapting%20differently.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMark%20Cuban%20says%20there's%20a%20simple%20explanation%20for%20why%20inflation%20hasn't%20risen%20as%20much%20as%20economists%20predicted%20in%20recent%20months%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20all%20comes%20down%20to%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20tariffs%20and%20the%20trade%20uncertainty%20they've%20triggered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20X%20post%20on%20Sunday%2C%20the%20billionaire%20entrepreneur%20said%20businesses%20are%20playing%20a%20high-stakes%20guessing%20game%20with%20tariffs%2C%20which%20is%20stopping%20them%20from%20raising%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20borrow%20money%20or%20use%20their%20available%20cash%20to%20front-run%20the%20tariffs%20and%20buy%20as%20much%20inventory%20as%20they%20can.%203%2C%206%20months%20or%20longer%2C%26quot%3B%20Cuban%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20kind%20of%20stockpiling%20is%20intended%20to%20lock%20in%20better%20prices%20ahead%20of%20potential%20tariff%20hikes%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20comes%20at%20a%20cost%2C%20Cuban%20said%3A%20using%20cash%20that%20could%20earn%20interest%20or%20taking%20on%20loans%20with%20high%20rates%2C%20sometimes%20between%2010%25%20and%2020%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECuban%20argued%20that%20this%20preemptive%20buying%20isn't%20a%20growth%20move%20but%20rather%20risk%20management.%20Companies%20are%20sacrificing%20financial%20flexibility%20just%20to%20stay%20ahead%20of%20unpredictable%20trade%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20because%20they%20don't%20know%20whether%20tariffs%20will%20rise%2C%20stay%20in%20place%2C%20or%20be%20rolled%20back%2C%20they're%20reluctant%20to%20pass%20on%20costs%20to%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20fact%2C%20they%20may%20even%20discount%20some%20as%20a%20way%20to%20clear%20out%20inventory%20and%20replenish%20cash%20or%20pay%20down%20expensive%20loans%2C%26quot%3B%20Cuban%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20strategy%2C%20he%20said%2C%20isn't%20limited%20to%20startups%20or%20small%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20all%20companies%20facing%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20Cuban%20added%2C%20noting%20that%20even%20Walmart%20has%20said%20price%20increases%20are%20more%20likely%20in%20the%20future%2C%20reflecting%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-raising-prices-increases-trump-tariffs-2025%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewait-and-see%20posture%20of%20many%20major%20firms%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20prices%20stay%20flatter%20than%20expected%2C%20even%20as%20other%20costs%20rise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Federal%20Reserve's%20favorite%20inflation%20measure%2C%20the%20personal%20consumption%20expenditures%20index%2C%20cooled%20in%20April%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-housing-costs-home-prices-rate-hikes-tariffs-mortgage-rates-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erising%20just%200.2%25%2C%20down%20from%20a%200.7%25%20jump%20in%20March%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20brought%20the%20annual%20inflation%20rate%20to%202.1%25%20in%20April%20%E2%80%94%20the%20lowest%20since%20March%202021%20and%20below%20consensus%20estimates%20of%202.2%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETreasury%20Secretary%20Scott%20Bessent%20echoed%20parts%20of%20Cuban's%20analysis%20in%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscott-bessent-dismisses-jamie-dimon-debt-concerns-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESunday%20appearance%20on%20CBS'%20%26quot%3BFace%20the%20Nation%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20but%20framed%20it%20more%20optimistically.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThus%20far%2C%20there%20have%20been%20no%20price%20increases%2C%26quot%3B%20Bessent%20said.%20%26quot%3BEverything%20has%20be